	<div class="how">
		<h4 class="how__title">Quartz</h4>
		<div class="how__third">
			<h5 class="how__sub-title">What do use in clocks now?</h5>
			<p class="how__paragraph">
				In 1972 we started using quartz crystals as a way to measure a second. When you "tap" quartz with an electric pulse it resonates
				at a specific frequency.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="how__third">
			<h5 class="how__sub-title">What makes quartz so special?</h5>
			<p class="how__paragraph">
				While many materials can be caused to resonate, quartz is a piezoelectric material. That means that when it resonates it
				produces electric pules of its own. We use those electric pulses as a sort of pendulum to keep time.
			</p>
		</div>
